Practical to cross 'het IJ' to Amsterdam North
Apr 2024 Solo
24/7 at least five crossings every hour, no charges. Pedestrians, bicycles, motorbikes are all admitted. Big improvement that motorized vehicles have to turn off their engines. Moreover, inside you are not exposed to wind, rain or snow.

It is one of the few public services for which you do not have to pay.
You have already paid the exorbitant taxes before.

Short but enjoyable ferry ride
Dec 2019
A free 5 minutes ferry ride from Centraal station to Bulksloterweg. The ferry ride was very stable and reliable and timely cruise between these 2 places. I think we took about 2 times during our entire trip in Amsterdam. First we were visiting This is Holland for a ground trip to the south Holland while 2nd time we visited Adam's lookout. There was a small shelter on the ferry allowing passengers to hide from sun and rain. We really enjoyed the free ride.
